      • embedOutput

        public BlurFactoryGeneric embedOutput(boolean autoAllowSignedValues,
                                      int bitDepth)
        Description copied from interface: ConvolutionFactoryBase
        Produces a GRAY16 image that can hold greater values than the original output image. The output image underlying this instance is replace by the new one. This allows operations such as difference or linear combination of images without overflows. If the original image is GRAY8, this is done by creating an image with 16 bits per pixel by copying the values without scaling (hence values are less than 256). If the original image is GRAY16, then the values are divided by 256 (hence values also are less than 256). If the resulting image is intended to allow for negative values (e.g. to compute differences), the gray levels are shifted by adding a value (Short.MAX_VALUE-Short.MIN_VALUE)/2 = 32767.
        Specified by:
        embedOutput in interface BlurFactory
        Specified by:
        embedOutput in interface ConvolutionFactoryBase
        Overrides:
        embedOutput in class ConvolutionFactoryBaseGeneric
        Parameters:
        autoAllowSignedValues - If true, the gray levels are shifted to start in the middle of the range of a short value.
        bitDepth - The target bit depth
        Returns:
        The reference to this instance to allow for use of the cascade pattern.
        See Also:
        ConvolutionFactoryBaseGeneric.embedOutput(boolean, int)

      • getIdentityMask

        public ConvolutionBaseGeneric getIdentityMask()
        Description copied from interface: BlurFactory
        Allows to get a convolution mask which has no effect on an image (Identity mask with mass one concentrated at 0). The image must be embedded so as to allow for addition of voxel values without any overflow. Use the method ImageSignPolicyEmbed.getImageEmbedding(boolean, int) if necessary to embed the image in a 16 bits images, and to divide values by 256 if the input image is already 16 bits.
        Specified by:
        getIdentityMask in interface BlurFactory
        Specified by:
        getIdentityMask in interface ConvolutionFactoryBase
        Overrides:
        getIdentityMask in class ConvolutionFactoryBaseGeneric
        Returns:
        A mask that does nothing with the same input and output buffer as this one.
        See Also:
        BlurFactory.getIdentityMask()

      • getBinomialBlurCalibrated

        public ConvolutionBase getBinomialBlurCalibrated(int nPointsX,
                                                 int nPointsY,
                                                 int nPointsZ,
                                                 double realSkippingStepX,
                                                 double realSkippingStepY,
                                                 double realSkippingStepZ,
                                                 VoxelDouble voxelEdgesLength)
        Description copied from interface: BlurFactory
        Constructs a Convolution Mask for Binomial Blur on the image with a mask characterized by a given support cardinality and a given skipping step (distance between to elements of the mask support) in each direction. This constructor does the same as BlurFactory.getBinomialBlur(int, int, int, int, int, int) except that the skipping steps are given in (approximately) multiples of the calibration data (Voxels edges lengths in a given length unit) instead of number of voxels.
        Specified by:
        getBinomialBlurCalibrated in interface BlurFactory
        Parameters:
        nPointsX - cardinality of the support of the smoothing mask; first coordinate
        nPointsY - cardinality of the support of the smoothing mask; second coordinate
        nPointsZ - cardinality of the support of the smoothing mask; second coordinate
        realSkippingStepX - Skipping step in X
        realSkippingStepY - Skipping step in Y
        realSkippingStepZ - Skipping step in Z
        voxelEdgesLength - The voxel's scale (edges' length) used as a factor to estimate actual skipping steps in each direction.
        Returns:
        The convolution mask ready to perform a binomial mask on the image underlying this instance.
        See Also:
        BlurFactory.getBinomialBlurCalibrated(int, int, int, double, double, double, VoxelDouble)
